Cell["\<\
Present a multi-sided argument with multiple causes using statistically \
significant evidence, with the correct distribution, priors. A case for the \
calibration bounded in probability space (using inequality bounds and via \
negativa) is to be given, as well as the outcome (concave upper bound, convex \
lower bound) in payoff space. Convexity problems, ergodicity and absorbing \
barrier arguments (cost benefit analysis), second order effects thought \
through the limit are to be accounted for. Problems that are not \
computationally reducible are to be recognised. A list of all rules and \
possible states/tokens are to be given, with suitable drawings of a multiway \
diagram drawn. Syllogisms using modus tollens are to be accounted for, with \
no affirming the consequent and denying the antecedent being done. There \
should be no begging the question, cherry picking, nit picking, anecdotes \
used as evidence. No verbalisms, all terms should have rigidity of meaning.\
\>", "Text",
